WEBVTT

00:01.403 --> 00:04.238
<i>♪ I can feel it</i>
<i>in my toes ♪</i>

00:04.240 --> 00:05.939
<i>♪ drop to the beat</i>
<i>like no one knows ♪</i>

00:05.942 --> 00:07.675
<i>♪ well, they don't know me</i>
<i>like that ♪</i>

00:07.677 --> 00:09.644
<i>♪ well, they don't</i>
<i>know me like that ♪</i>

00:09.646 --> 00:12.647
<i>♪ oh, I am never gonna stop ♪</i>

00:12.649 --> 00:13.781
<i>♪ all the haters</i>
<i>gonna see me on top ♪</i>

00:13.783 --> 00:16.484
[gasps]
Uh-oh.

00:16.486 --> 00:17.852
Guys, guys.

00:17.854 --> 00:19.654
Our worst nightmare's
come true.

00:19.656 --> 00:20.788
It's Isabela's birthday.

00:20.790 --> 00:22.223
You always
do that joke.

00:22.225 --> 00:23.624
I know,
'cause it's so funny,

00:23.626 --> 00:25.059
but this time,
it's for real.

00:25.061 --> 00:26.360
That's not good.

00:26.362 --> 00:27.762
- Are you sure?
- Yeah!

00:27.764 --> 00:29.163
Her agent
sent her flowers.

00:29.165 --> 00:31.299
all: - Oh.
- This is not a drill.

00:31.301 --> 00:32.266
So what do we do?

00:32.268 --> 00:33.668
We survive.

00:33.670 --> 00:35.202
We know she's going
to be in a bad mood,

00:35.204 --> 00:37.071
so that means don't talk to her,
don't touch her,

00:37.073 --> 00:38.439
don't even think about her!

00:38.441 --> 00:39.640
(whispers)
She'll know!

00:41.611 --> 00:44.145
- Coffee, now.
- Whoa!

00:44.147 --> 00:45.680
Good luck, everyone.

00:49.319 --> 00:50.518
All right,
let's get this over with

00:50.520 --> 00:52.453
before I forget
my one line.

00:52.455 --> 00:54.155
One line,
can you believe it?

00:54.157 --> 00:55.723
I'm an award-winning actress.

00:55.725 --> 00:58.960
I've been doing telenovelas
for 20 years...

00:58.962 --> 01:02.229
which is remarkable
considering how young I am.

01:02.231 --> 01:03.931
How young are you?

01:03.933 --> 01:05.967
- [hisses]
- [gasps]

01:05.969 --> 01:07.134
Any guesses?

01:07.136 --> 01:08.736
- 112?
- 35?

01:08.738 --> 01:10.237
Here's your coffee.

01:12.141 --> 01:14.642
I said almond milk!

01:14.644 --> 01:15.610
[grunts]

01:15.612 --> 01:16.844
Ow!
She did it again!

01:16.846 --> 01:18.813
All right, calm down,
Cruella de Vil.

01:18.815 --> 01:20.181
We all know it's
your birthday.

01:20.183 --> 01:21.882
Don't you think
you're overreacting?

01:23.686 --> 01:26.420
[sighs]

01:26.422 --> 01:28.389
You're right.

01:28.391 --> 01:29.991
What is wrong with me?

01:29.993 --> 01:33.294
You know, my father left us
on my sixth birthday,

01:33.296 --> 01:37.498
and I always thought,
"If I were only prettier

01:37.500 --> 01:40.601
or smarter,
he would've come back."

01:40.603 --> 01:43.871
I guess when I lash out,
it's just me saying,

01:43.873 --> 01:45.539
"Love me, Daddy."

01:47.310 --> 01:49.243
Oh, Isabela.

01:49.245 --> 01:51.345
I had no idea.

01:51.347 --> 01:54.915
And that, bitches,
is how you act.

01:54.917 --> 01:57.852
<i>[flamenco guitar music]</i>

01:57.854 --> 01:59.787
She didn't--
she didn't get me.

01:59.789 --> 02:01.322
She got me.

02:01.324 --> 02:04.325
<i>[upbeat Spanish music]</i>

02:04.327 --> 02:07.054
Sync and corrections by n17t01
www.addic7ed.com

02:12.368 --> 02:14.101
[grunts]

02:14.103 --> 02:16.504
I hate that Isabela tricked us
into having feelings for her.

02:16.506 --> 02:18.339
I know.
For a minute there,

02:18.341 --> 02:20.708
I thought she had blood pumping
through her cold, dead heart.

02:20.710 --> 02:22.977
I just hate secrets.
They ruin relationships.

02:22.979 --> 02:24.478
It's true.

02:24.480 --> 02:26.113
My ex-husband told secrets,
and now he's in jail.

02:26.115 --> 02:28.049
Yeah, my last boyfriend
told me he was naturally blond,

02:28.051 --> 02:29.850
but then in the winter,
when his body hair grew back.

02:29.852 --> 02:31.118
I found that it
was all a lie.

02:31.120 --> 02:32.553
Exactly.

02:32.555 --> 02:34.455
You know, we spend
so much time together.

02:34.457 --> 02:35.723
How are we supposed
to be a family

02:35.725 --> 02:37.224
if we can't trust each other?

02:37.226 --> 02:38.793
Get me up, Mimi.

02:38.795 --> 02:40.494
- [grunts]
- Okay.

02:40.496 --> 02:42.329
Oh, all right,
everybody!

02:42.331 --> 02:44.031
I have an announcement.

02:45.401 --> 02:46.534
Just--

02:46.536 --> 02:47.935
really quick.

02:47.937 --> 02:49.503
Why isn't anybody gathering?

02:49.505 --> 02:51.205
You've been making a lot
of announcements lately.

02:51.207 --> 02:52.873
People are starting
to get bored.

02:52.875 --> 02:55.910
You might have to entice
them with something.

02:55.912 --> 02:56.877
Hmm.

02:56.879 --> 02:58.713
Ice cream for everyone.

02:58.715 --> 03:00.481
And since you're all here,

03:00.483 --> 03:03.684
I want to give you encouragement
to share more of yourselves.

03:03.686 --> 03:05.786
I want us to stay
a tight-knit family,

03:05.788 --> 03:08.689
so from now on, we're going to
have an open-book policy.

03:08.691 --> 03:10.658
No more secrets, okay?

03:10.660 --> 03:12.293
I'll be the first to share.

03:12.295 --> 03:16.263
I once broke my thumb playing
with a very strong baby.

03:16.265 --> 03:17.398
Anyone else want to share?

03:17.400 --> 03:19.433
Okay.
My wife just left me.

03:19.435 --> 03:21.635
Maybe let's just start with
the fun stuff, to ease in.

03:21.637 --> 03:23.070
I own two Segways.

03:23.072 --> 03:24.472
Fun!
[chuckles]

03:24.474 --> 03:26.340
Unnecessary
but fun.

03:26.342 --> 03:29.410
Oh, when I get stressed out,
I eat chalk.

03:29.412 --> 03:30.578
His wife left him for me.

03:30.580 --> 03:32.246
Okay, you know what?

03:32.248 --> 03:33.914
We're gonna--
we're gonna find our groove.

03:33.916 --> 03:35.916
But great sharing, you guys.
Good job.

03:37.286 --> 03:39.153
- Doesn't go all the way up?
- Nope.

03:39.155 --> 03:40.488
I don't know what happened.

03:40.490 --> 03:42.089
It was fine yesterday
in the killer bee scene,

03:42.091 --> 03:43.991
but today
it just got stuck.

03:43.993 --> 03:45.493
It's a tricky little guy.

03:45.495 --> 03:47.962
I mean, big guy.
I-- I wouldn't know.

03:47.964 --> 03:49.263
How would I know?

03:49.265 --> 03:50.698
Would it be easier
if I took the pants off?

03:50.700 --> 03:52.900
[laughs nervously]

03:52.902 --> 03:54.468
Okay, thanks.

03:54.470 --> 03:57.204
[still laughing nervously]

03:57.206 --> 03:58.472
If you're trying on
new laughs,

03:58.474 --> 04:00.307
I'd have a back-up option.

04:00.309 --> 04:01.709
Well, what sound
should I make

04:01.711 --> 04:03.344
when I'm feeling up
my co-worker?

04:03.346 --> 04:04.478
So what's going on
with you?

04:04.480 --> 04:05.646
Hmm.

04:05.648 --> 04:07.782
Come on.
Open-book policy.

04:07.784 --> 04:11.118
Last night, I had a sex dream
about Rodrigo.

04:11.120 --> 04:12.920
- What?
- We were on the beach.

04:12.922 --> 04:14.688
And there were all these
dolphins watching.

04:14.690 --> 04:16.055
They were really pervy too,

04:16.058 --> 04:17.791
because they kept
high-fiving each other, like--

04:17.793 --> 04:19.360
[imitates dolphins]

04:19.362 --> 04:20.928
- Dolphins are pervy.
- Mm.

04:20.930 --> 04:22.730
Xavi and I were snorkeling
in the Bahamas,

04:22.732 --> 04:24.532
and one of them stuck
their tongue in my ear.

04:24.534 --> 04:26.100
- Ew.
- Mm.

04:26.102 --> 04:28.235
So you have a thing
for Rodrigo?

04:28.237 --> 04:30.838
No, it's just been a long time
since I've, you know--

04:30.840 --> 04:32.439
[clicks tongue]

04:32.441 --> 04:34.441
If you think that's sex,
it has been a long time.

04:34.443 --> 04:35.676
Tell me about it.

04:35.678 --> 04:37.244
Well, if it's sex you need,

04:37.246 --> 04:38.579
why don't you sleep
with Rodrigo?

04:38.581 --> 04:40.181
Are you kidding?

04:40.183 --> 04:42.349
Have you seen the girls
he's brought around here?

04:42.351 --> 04:44.652
I've pumped out three kids,
I dye my gray hair,

04:44.654 --> 04:46.754
and I've got that weird scar
from the mechanical bull.

04:46.756 --> 04:49.323
I told you you were
riding it backwards.

04:49.325 --> 04:51.992
- Mimi, you're beautiful.
- Yeah, but I'm not his type.

04:51.994 --> 04:53.627
And, you know, that's okay.

04:53.629 --> 04:56.463
I'm too busy for all this
middle school crush crap.

04:56.465 --> 04:58.332
I'm happy with just
the fantasy.

04:58.334 --> 05:00.534
Reality requires
too much free time.

05:00.536 --> 05:01.969
And waxing.

05:03.940 --> 05:05.840
[gasps]

05:05.842 --> 05:08.776
<i>[ominous music]</i>

05:08.778 --> 05:16.750
<i>♪
♪</i>

05:18.020 --> 05:20.955
Hello, Mr... Belvedere.

05:20.957 --> 05:24.692
<i>♪
♪</i>

05:24.694 --> 05:26.861
Looks like you walked
into a dead zone.

05:26.863 --> 05:28.162
<i>[flamenco guitar music]</i>

05:28.164 --> 05:30.197
All right, clear the set.

05:30.199 --> 05:32.600
Rehearsing for tomorrow's
big stunt.

05:32.602 --> 05:34.201
I love when we do stunts.

05:34.203 --> 05:36.237
There are so many
fun toys on set!

05:36.239 --> 05:38.472
Breakaway bottles.

05:38.474 --> 05:40.841
Breakaway chairs.

05:40.843 --> 05:42.276
Ooh, breakaway glasses--

05:42.278 --> 05:43.544
Actually, those are Karen's!

05:43.546 --> 05:46.113
Oops.

05:46.115 --> 05:47.648
Sorry.
Sorry.

05:50.753 --> 05:52.086
Yep, that should hold.

05:52.088 --> 05:54.755
Tomorrow, my character
darts into the room,

05:54.757 --> 05:57.524
leaps over this couch, and jumps
through that glass window.

05:57.526 --> 05:59.760
You're doing all that?
You're so brave!

05:59.762 --> 06:01.629
[laughs].
I'm not doing all that.

06:01.631 --> 06:03.163
Got to protect the merch.

06:03.165 --> 06:04.465
That's why we have stunt guys--

06:04.467 --> 06:06.133
Big, brawny dudes
that are so tough,

06:06.135 --> 06:07.801
they can run through a window
and not even feel it.

06:07.803 --> 06:10.137
Xavi, I would like you
to meet your stunt double.

06:10.139 --> 06:11.538
Hi, I'm Colleen.

06:13.476 --> 06:15.509
Oh, she's so cute!

06:18.481 --> 06:20.114
I got it.

06:24.453 --> 06:26.520
- Here you go, mami.
- [laughs nervously]

06:27.623 --> 06:30.057
[mouthing silently]

06:30.059 --> 06:31.558
Are you playing Charades
without me?

06:31.560 --> 06:33.994
One word, movie,
four syllables, "Armageddon"!

06:33.996 --> 06:35.462
Shh!

06:35.464 --> 06:37.131
- Hey, Rodrigo.
- Yo.

06:37.133 --> 06:38.732
Doesn't Mimi look
pretty today?

06:38.734 --> 06:40.200
- [laughs nervously]
- Of course.

06:40.202 --> 06:41.902
A strong, worldly,
sophisticated woman--

06:41.904 --> 06:43.070
she always looks beautiful.

06:43.072 --> 06:44.838
[chuckles]

06:44.840 --> 06:47.174
- Would you sleep with her?
- Ana!

06:47.176 --> 06:48.776
What?
Hypothetically.

06:48.778 --> 06:51.078
No. I would
make love to her.

06:51.080 --> 06:53.614
[laughs nervously]

06:53.616 --> 06:55.749
Screw your
open-book policy.

06:55.751 --> 06:58.252
Oh, Mimi!

06:58.254 --> 07:00.621
Oh, Mimi's mad at Ana?

07:00.623 --> 07:02.623
Happy birthday to me.

07:02.625 --> 07:04.391
[scoffs]
Isabela.

07:04.393 --> 07:06.927
There's no one
worse than her.

07:06.929 --> 07:08.095
[both gasp]

07:08.097 --> 07:11.465
<i>[flamenco guitar music]</i>

07:11.467 --> 07:14.535
Happy birthday
to both of us, sister.

07:16.138 --> 07:18.472
- Carmen!
- Hello, Isabela.

07:18.474 --> 07:25.546
<i>♪
♪</i>

07:26.916 --> 07:30.851
I miss you so much!
[cries]

07:31.954 --> 07:34.755
It's a birthday miracle.

07:34.757 --> 07:37.091
Look how happy
everyone is.

07:37.093 --> 07:38.993
I'm so scared.

07:38.995 --> 07:41.128
<i>Hi, this is Mimi. Please leave</i>
<i>a message after the--</i>

07:41.130 --> 07:43.964
<i>Ow! Nico, are you kidding me?</i>
<i>Throwing a--</i>

07:43.966 --> 07:46.100
Mimi, I've called you
four times.

07:46.102 --> 07:48.769
We have to talk about
Isabela's crazy twin!

07:48.771 --> 07:51.372
[sighs] Hope you're not
asleep already.

07:53.009 --> 07:57.111
It's 8:30, so maybe.
All right, well, call me.

07:57.113 --> 08:00.647
<i>[funky music]</i>

08:00.649 --> 08:02.416
Let's do that again.

08:02.418 --> 08:03.984
Okay.

08:03.986 --> 08:05.853
This is so much better
without the dolphins watching.

08:05.855 --> 08:06.920
Hmm?

08:10.148 --> 08:13.877
- <i> ♪ I'm walking on sunshine ♪</i>
- Woot woot!

08:13.964 --> 08:17.119
- Somebody's in a good mood.
- Somebody got a little <i>acción.</i>

08:17.121 --> 08:19.222
Had a one-night stand
with Rodrigo.

08:19.224 --> 08:22.158
[gasps]
Ow. What?

08:22.160 --> 08:25.962
It was exactly what I needed--
a no-strings-attached good time.

08:25.964 --> 08:27.997
Oh, I'm so happy for you!

08:27.999 --> 08:31.400
Open-book policy works!
Tell me all the details!

08:31.402 --> 08:33.736
Okay, first of all,
he has, like, the best body.

08:33.738 --> 08:36.371
Oh!
[gags]

08:36.374 --> 08:37.807
Continue.

08:37.808 --> 08:39.342
And then he does this thing
where he kind of

08:39.344 --> 08:40.510
revs up like an engine.

08:40.511 --> 08:42.778
Vroom! Vroom!

08:42.780 --> 08:45.815
[laughs]
[gags]

08:45.817 --> 08:47.850
Is something wrong?

08:47.852 --> 08:49.919
You guys are basically like
my brother and sister.

08:49.921 --> 08:51.420
Maybe if you
told me in code,

08:51.422 --> 08:53.322
like you're an apple
and he's an orange.

08:53.324 --> 08:54.657
Okay, well,
you know how an orange

08:54.659 --> 08:55.992
has that hard, nubby part?

08:55.994 --> 08:57.793
[gags]
No more.

08:57.795 --> 08:59.328
Fair enough.
Just don't tell anybody

08:59.330 --> 09:01.063
we had a one-night
stand, okay?

09:01.065 --> 09:02.798
Don't worry.
Your secret's safe with me.

09:02.800 --> 09:04.200
Okay.

09:04.202 --> 09:07.136
- You slept with Rodrigo?
- Starting now.

09:07.138 --> 09:08.204
I only texted Gael!

09:08.206 --> 09:09.672
Well, how did you do that?

09:09.674 --> 09:11.574
We've maintained eye contact
this whole time.

09:11.576 --> 09:12.975
I have a talent.

09:12.977 --> 09:15.011
I'm ordering shoes right now.

09:16.981 --> 09:18.981
I'm gonna need
all the details.

09:20.184 --> 09:22.785
Okay, I didn't need
all the details.

09:24.656 --> 09:26.155
Oh, no.

09:26.157 --> 09:27.757
Hello, Gael.

09:27.759 --> 09:30.826
It's me, Isabela,
not my identical twin.

09:30.828 --> 09:32.662
Oh, thank you for
letting me know,

09:32.664 --> 09:36.265
as your twin looks in no way,
shape, or form younger than you.

09:36.267 --> 09:42.138
Carmen, this is Gael,
my sweet little co-star.

09:42.140 --> 09:43.372
[all laugh]

09:43.374 --> 09:45.741
So why have we not
met Carmen before?

09:45.743 --> 09:48.878
Well, growing up, we were the
Olsen twins of the novela world.

09:48.880 --> 09:51.447
And then we were both up
for the same part in a movie.

09:51.449 --> 09:53.215
Isabela got it, of course,

09:53.217 --> 09:55.251
and I was a bit
of a sore loser.

09:55.253 --> 09:57.553
Oh, you would've brought
so much more to the role.

09:57.555 --> 09:59.322
And I don't mean that
as a fat joke.

09:59.324 --> 10:01.657
She was a half pound more
than me when we were born.

10:01.659 --> 10:05.094
Oh, stop! I'm just so glad
we're finally moving past this.

10:05.096 --> 10:07.997
I thought I lost
my sister forever.

10:07.999 --> 10:10.232
You don't know how much
this means to me.

10:10.234 --> 10:12.301
[cries]

10:12.303 --> 10:15.504
[sobbing]

10:15.506 --> 10:17.139
Look at me,
crying like my housekeeper

10:17.141 --> 10:19.342
when I yelled at her for
using the good bathroom.

10:19.344 --> 10:21.143
I have to get
cleaned up.

10:21.145 --> 10:23.879
I'm shooting a scene
where I wake from a coma,

10:23.881 --> 10:25.848
but when I bolt up,
I hit my head

10:25.850 --> 10:27.216
and I fall back into a coma.

10:27.218 --> 10:28.284
Oh!

10:30.488 --> 10:33.990
Oh, Gael, I've missed
so many years with my sister.

10:33.992 --> 10:37.827
Fill me in-- what's it like
working with Isabela?

10:37.829 --> 10:42.131
- It's, uh--
- Oh, I know that look.

10:42.133 --> 10:46.135
Isabela is the best, but
sometimes she can be... prickly.

10:46.137 --> 10:47.303
[laughs nervously]

10:47.305 --> 10:48.938
You know, when we were six,

10:48.940 --> 10:51.007
she kidnapped my teddy bear
and held it for ransom.

10:51.009 --> 10:54.210
Oh, my God, she did the same
thing to my asthma inhaler.

10:54.212 --> 10:57.246
[laughs]
She's crazy!

10:58.383 --> 11:00.016
- Hey, Rodrigo.
- Yo.

11:00.018 --> 11:02.151
- Do you use a stunt double?
- [scoffs] No.

11:02.153 --> 11:03.419
I do my own stunts.

11:03.421 --> 11:04.987
People call me
the Latino Jackie Chan.

11:04.989 --> 11:06.288
Really?

11:06.290 --> 11:07.957
If I say it enough,
it'll catch on.

11:07.959 --> 11:09.425
Yeah, I'm thinking about
doing my own stunts too.

11:09.427 --> 11:11.527
Oh, he's just embarrassed

11:11.529 --> 11:13.095
because his stunt man
is a woman,

11:13.097 --> 11:15.264
but that's nothing
to be ashamed of.

11:15.266 --> 11:17.600
Tell him, Rodrigo.

11:17.602 --> 11:20.703
[laughs]

11:20.705 --> 11:23.172
A woman?

11:23.174 --> 11:25.107
A woman!

11:25.109 --> 11:26.142
It's not funny.

11:26.144 --> 11:27.643
What's wrong?

11:27.645 --> 11:29.378
They keep teasing me
about my stunt person.

11:29.380 --> 11:31.514
Oh, well, you need a good one,
you can use mine.

11:31.516 --> 11:35.017
- Her name's Colleen.
- [laughs]

11:35.019 --> 11:37.586
You do have
the same stunt person!

11:37.588 --> 11:40.256
[laughing]

11:40.258 --> 11:41.857
That was funny.

11:45.630 --> 11:47.296
- Good coffee.
- Yeah.

11:51.836 --> 11:54.503
- I made love to Mimi.
- Yes! [laughs]

11:54.505 --> 11:56.639
Now that you know that I know,
we can both talk about it.

11:56.641 --> 11:59.141
- She was so wild.
- [gags]

11:59.143 --> 12:01.977
I'm sorry, by "talk,"
I mean in the general sense.

12:01.979 --> 12:03.746
- You happy? Things good?
- Oh, yeah, very.

12:03.748 --> 12:05.748
You see? My open-book
theory was right!

12:05.750 --> 12:07.183
You and Mimi
put it out there

12:07.185 --> 12:09.785
that you were attracted
to each other, and voila!

12:09.787 --> 12:11.821
Casual one-night stand
