affect my work?

12:43.468 --> 12:46.769
[scoffs] [scoffs]
Ridiculous.

12:46.771 --> 12:48.371
[sighs]
We had a good run.

12:48.373 --> 12:50.072
Oh, come on.

12:50.074 --> 12:52.308
Be a man and let
the little girl do your stunt.

12:52.310 --> 12:53.843
- No.
- Fine.

12:53.845 --> 12:55.611
But if you're going
face first,

12:55.613 --> 12:57.747
try to lead with the forehead,
because the nose?

12:57.749 --> 13:01.617
Oy, it'll shatter instantly.

13:01.619 --> 13:05.521
Okay, here we go.
Places!

13:05.523 --> 13:06.889
And action!

13:06.891 --> 13:09.859
<i>[flamenco guitar music]</i>

13:09.861 --> 13:14.897
<i>♪
♪</i>

13:14.899 --> 13:17.033
Rodrigo,
what are you doing?

13:17.035 --> 13:18.167
Choke me.

13:18.169 --> 13:20.169
Come on.

13:20.171 --> 13:21.938
[tiny whimper]

13:21.940 --> 13:24.774
I can't do this,
not with her here.

13:24.776 --> 13:26.976
Her who?
Me? What did I do?

13:26.978 --> 13:28.444
It's what
you didn't do,

13:28.446 --> 13:30.813
i.e., treat me
with respect.

13:30.815 --> 13:33.249
You know, "one-night stand,"
you called it?

13:33.251 --> 13:36.352
Yeah, yeah, surprise, everybody.
Mimi and I slept together.

13:36.354 --> 13:37.653
- Oh!
- [people murmur]

13:37.655 --> 13:39.121
I may have just been
a body to you,

13:39.123 --> 13:42.291
but this body has feelings!

13:42.293 --> 13:44.226
- [exhales]
- [laughs nervously]

13:44.228 --> 13:46.362
I know that looks bad.

13:46.364 --> 13:49.031
Uh, are we not
going to do the stunt?

13:49.033 --> 13:50.967
Cool, cool.

13:50.969 --> 13:53.002
I was totally ready.

13:53.004 --> 13:55.972
So Isabela kicked
the whole group of school kids

13:55.974 --> 13:57.073
out of the building.

13:57.075 --> 13:58.407
I believe her quote was,

13:58.409 --> 14:00.376
"Do you want to be
an at-risk youth?

14:00.378 --> 14:02.211
Try smiling at me again."

14:02.213 --> 14:04.981
[both laugh]

14:04.983 --> 14:06.649
Between you and me,
it's a blast

14:06.651 --> 14:10.353
to chat with someone who hates
Isabela just as much as I do.

14:10.355 --> 14:13.356
Whoa, I don't
hate Isabela.

14:13.358 --> 14:18.594
Mm, I have 45 minutes on here
that suggest otherwise.

14:18.596 --> 14:20.696
<i>And then she switched</i>
<i>my hair gel with honey,</i>

14:20.698 --> 14:23.532
<i>which is how I found out</i>
<i>I was allergic to bees.</i>

14:23.534 --> 14:24.934
You've been recording me?

14:24.936 --> 14:26.602
Yes!

14:26.604 --> 14:29.238
I had to delete my daughter's
baby pictures to make room.

14:29.240 --> 14:31.007
But it was worth it.

14:31.009 --> 14:32.875
When my tell-all book
comes out,

14:32.877 --> 14:34.543
Isabela's life
will be destroyed.

14:34.545 --> 14:36.679
You are writing
a mean book?

14:36.681 --> 14:38.014
You're not here
to make peace?

14:38.016 --> 14:39.315
I'm here to ruin
Isabela's life

14:39.317 --> 14:41.183
like she ruined mine.

14:41.185 --> 14:45.321
And thanks to you,
I'm already on chapter five.

14:45.323 --> 14:47.023
[gasps]

14:47.025 --> 14:49.558
I can't believe
you're the evil twin!

14:51.629 --> 14:53.429
[whimpers]

14:53.431 --> 14:55.031
Are you still
mad at me?

14:55.033 --> 14:57.233
You said you were going to
keep my secret to yourself.

14:57.235 --> 15:01.170
I feel terrible, but Rodrigo
told me about your night.

15:01.172 --> 15:02.471
He knew maybe I'd know,

15:02.473 --> 15:03.973
and I knew you knew he knew,

15:03.975 --> 15:06.208
so, really,
we all knew, you know?

15:06.210 --> 15:07.877
Why do secrets
have so many rules?

15:07.879 --> 15:11.647
Ana, just admit it!
Your open-book policy is stupid.

15:11.649 --> 15:14.784
Or if everybody told each
other everything at all times,

15:14.786 --> 15:16.285
we wouldn't be
having this fight.

15:16.287 --> 15:18.421
Okay, you want
to know everything?

15:18.423 --> 15:20.423
Rodrigo and I had sex
three times last night.

15:20.425 --> 15:23.259
And after each time it ended,
he'd say, "And scene."

15:23.261 --> 15:24.860
Ah, okay, I admit it!

15:24.862 --> 15:26.395
My open-book theory's wrong.

15:26.397 --> 15:28.064
Ana, your open-book
theory is wrong.

15:28.066 --> 15:29.632
I know;
I just said that.

15:29.634 --> 15:31.867
Oh. Well, why didn't you
tell me that earlier?

15:31.869 --> 15:34.737
Thanks to your advice, I was an
open book with Isabela's twin,

15:34.739 --> 15:37.239
and now there's an actual book,
a tell-all book

15:37.241 --> 15:38.874
full of all the dirt
I gave her.

15:38.876 --> 15:40.543
Oh, my God,
that's awful!

15:40.545 --> 15:43.045
Ana, fix this,
or else I'll tell you

15:43.047 --> 15:45.381
that Rodrigo likes toes,
specifically all ten of my toes,

15:45.383 --> 15:46.916
shoved in his mouth.

15:46.918 --> 15:48.784
[gags] Okay!
All right, I'll fix it!

15:53.958 --> 15:55.591
There she is.

15:55.593 --> 15:57.426
That phone has all
of Isabela's stories on it.

15:57.428 --> 15:58.761
She's leaving.
Stop her!

15:58.763 --> 16:00.362
How am I supposed
to do that?

16:00.364 --> 16:02.431
You're a cop on the show.
Do what he'd do.

16:04.268 --> 16:06.502
Oh, for crying out loud.
Come on!

16:06.504 --> 16:08.304
Carmen!

16:08.306 --> 16:10.606
Sorry, Carmen, we're not letting
you leave with that phone.

16:10.608 --> 16:12.541
Oh?
So the secret's out.

16:12.543 --> 16:14.376
Figured you'd be
on board, Ana.

16:14.378 --> 16:17.113
According to Gael, most of
Isabela's fights involve you.

16:17.115 --> 16:19.415
Isabela and I have
a complicated relationship.

16:19.417 --> 16:20.983
Most of the time,
we hate each other.

16:20.985 --> 16:22.752
But last year, she held
the door open for me.

16:22.754 --> 16:24.286
I mean, she thought
I was someone else,

16:24.288 --> 16:26.288
but she is part
of the show,

16:26.290 --> 16:27.957
and I will not let you
embarrass her.

16:27.959 --> 16:30.292
Not even if I tell you
how old we are?

16:30.294 --> 16:32.495
[inhales]
Ooh, that's a tough one.

16:32.497 --> 16:34.964
- It is.
- Yeah.

16:34.966 --> 16:36.732
No.

16:36.734 --> 16:39.535
But could you narrow it down
to a decade?

16:39.537 --> 16:41.771
- Ooh, give me that.
- Get it, Ana. Get it. Get it.

16:41.773 --> 16:43.005
- No!
- Ana, get it. Get it!

16:43.007 --> 16:44.340
You can help me,
you know.

16:44.342 --> 16:45.841
Give me it!

16:45.843 --> 16:48.577
What is going on here?

16:48.579 --> 16:50.780
You know you're talking
to Carmen, right?

16:50.782 --> 16:53.249
- I'm Isabela.
- Oh, Isabela, thank God.

16:53.251 --> 16:55.251
I was trying to stop
these lunatics

16:55.253 --> 16:58.187
from saying such hurtful things
about you, and they attacked me.

16:58.189 --> 17:00.489
She's lying!
She's not here to make peace.

17:00.491 --> 17:02.591
She's writing
a tell-all book about you.

17:02.593 --> 17:04.059
Who are you gonna believe--

17:04.060 --> 17:07.762
these two
or your twin sister?

17:09.634 --> 17:12.134
Carmen...

17:12.136 --> 17:13.569
you're my twin,

17:13.570 --> 17:15.570
my other half.

17:15.573 --> 17:19.074
It has killed me to be apart
from you for so long,

17:19.076 --> 17:21.242
all because I got
that movie part.

17:21.244 --> 17:23.112
Why couldn't it
have been you?

17:25.049 --> 17:28.284
Oh, right.
Because I'm the better actor.

17:29.387 --> 17:30.452
Ooh!

17:32.056 --> 17:35.891
Oh, that was
a big mistake.

17:35.893 --> 17:37.159
<i>[flamenco guitar music]</i>

17:37.161 --> 17:39.395
- Oh.
- God.

17:39.397 --> 17:41.230
Well, we should do something.

17:42.600 --> 17:45.935
Ah, yeah.
I got it.

17:45.937 --> 17:47.203
Oh, this is good.
This is good.

17:49.362 --> 17:51.629
